entries.femaleVariant: Mm! Woman of the hour! Sheesh, it took you long enough! Worked up an appetite just waitin'!
entries.maleVariant: Mm! Man of the hour! Heheh, sheesh – took you long enough! Worked up an appetite just waiting!

entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="mex" o="Gracias a dios. ¡Estoy lleno!" t="Thank God. I'm stuffed!" b="" a=""/>
We'll see about that...
Let's feel this factory-new ride.
Siddown, lemme finish this. Then we can drop in on Señor Vektor.
[Take] Thanks.
Prolly both 'cause you usually forget shit. But it just so happens, I think I mighta bagged us a sweet-ass J-O-B.
Mentioned somethin' about a surprise yesterday. 'M I rememberin' right or... just had a brain fart?
I mean, maybe it's not as big as that, but... Just that it's fronted by a little-known someone named Dexter DeShawn.
Only the top fixer in Night-fuckin'-City! Fat-assed Black Jesus of the Afterlife. Three hundred pounds of partly gold-plated cool.
Oh, was supposed to stop by Vik's anyhow. I got a date – me and Misty.
Didn't figure you as the type for Asian. Woulda thought you'd find it too exotic.
Whaddaya mean? What's there not to like?
Noodles – check. Synthsirloin – check. Get some more chili action up in here, and you're lookin' at Mama Welles' signature sopa de fideos, hahah!
What's the job, exactly?
Go on...
How'd you manage this?
Dex ain't outta the picture?
How did you manage to pull this? Trade in your spleen or something? Far as I know, we're not the type to get fingered by Dex.
entries.maleVariant: How'd you manage to pull this? Trade in your spleen or somethin'? Far as I know, we're not the type to get fingered by Dex.

entries.femaleVariant: You, me – nah. But T-Bug – she's the one that hooked us up, got us talkin'. Knew it was a done deal the moment he laid eyes on me.
'Cause, c'mon – ain't nobody who can resist this. Am I right?
Heh, sure, Jack. Whatever you say.
Tell me more about Dex.
Thought Dex bounced outta the ring a few years ago. Messed with a nasty crew in Pacifica, things got ugly.
Mhm. Gang wars two years back. Somehow Dex got caught up in the craziness. Lotta bodies lyin' in the streets by the time the shootin' stopped.
Eh, Dex got lucky, though. Managed to slip under the radar till tempers cooled. Took a while… but he's made one hell of a comeback.
Guy's up to his elbows in blood, Jack. And you wanna shake his hand, work with him.
entries.maleVariant: Guy's up to his elbows in blood, Jack. And you wanna shake his hand, work with him?

entries.femaleVariant: This is it, Jackie – our big break.
This is it, Jackie – our break. Dex needs friends, needs us, we can use him.
Something about this stinks.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="Amen, " a=". It's a win-win."/>
entries.maleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="ese" b="Amen, " a=". It's a win-win."/>

entries.femaleVariant: It's the biz, V. Everyone's got blood on their hands. You deal with it, you move on.
So what's the gig? We meant to come out in one piece?
Dexter DeShawn... What's the latest spec on him? Know you got info to spill.
entries.maleVariant: Dexter DeShawn…? What's the latest spec on him? Know you got info to spill.

entries.femaleVariant: He's been off the grid for about two years. Word on the street was... he took a little vacay.
Two years? That's exile, not a vacation. Hell was he up to?
Aa, guessin' he shoved pizzas in his mouth while jerkin' off to hardcore virtus. Important thing is he's back, needs a fresh crew and he found us.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="Well, our savior wants to tell you everything himself. Face to face. No pressure, but... whole deal's ridin' on you now, " a="."/>
entries.maleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="ese" b="Our lord and savior wants to tell you everything himself. Face to face. Oh, no pressure, but, uh... this whole deal? 'S ridin' on you now, " a="."/>

entries.femaleVariant: Don't see why not.
Wait, why me?
All right. Let's hear what old Dex has to say. Set it up.
entries.maleVariant: All right. Let's hear what ol' Dex has to say. Set it up.

entries.femaleVariant: Why do I gotta go? You and T-Bug draw straws without me?
T-Bug and Dex go way back. And my face is yesterday's news. Aw, Dex says he needs to check you, talk to you.
Look, V, it's his job, his rules. I can't blame 'im for takin' a personal approach. An' it ain't as bad as you think, OK? Trust me.
Guess I got no choice, then.
Some top-notch work, Miguel did. Rides like it looks – factory new.
So we rollin' or what?
You don't say…
She's sooo sweet. Really gets me, y'know?
First stop – ripperdoc?
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="An', " a=", easy on the gas, 'ey? I just ate."/>
entries.maleVariant: An', holmes, easy on the gas, uh? I just ate.

entries.femaleVariant: Aa, this is it! C'mon, V.
[Stand] Let's go.
Find me once Vik's done dustin' your circuits. We'll hash out what Dex's cooked up for us.
Brought your wheels. Gave 'em to my guy yesterday to smooth over the dents after our, uh, dust-up with the scavs.
Dex is the real deal when it comes to fixers. Don't get me wrong, don't got nothin' against the Padre or Wakako, but... Dex is in a league of his own. You know what I'm sayin'?
Not really.
Know my way around fixers.
Not really, no.
It's always the same story. You land on fresh turf, local fixer waves his dick around, but... he's smilin' – sayin' you'll be up to your neck in gigs and eddies.
Still, all you are's another name in their little black book. Nifty tool for gettin' them a fat slice o' whatever half-baked shitpie their client put on the table.
Don't get me started on fixers. They catch a client, find the cheapest gonk to do the job, then drop their corpse at a landfill.
Shit. Hit the nail on the head, V.
Sure, you crack jokes over drinks, but in the end… it's biz.
Thanks, Jack. Much appreciated.
Whatcha eatin'?
[Sit] Said you had a surprise for me?
